metadata:
  section_id: 9
  section_name: رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
  hadith_first: 54
  hadith_last: 69

hadiths[15]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
54,"""You must apply antimony, for it clears the vision and makes the eyelashes grow.”",,,54,"Ibn 'Umar said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
55,"""The apparel dearest to Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was the shirt [qamis].”",,,55,"Umm ul Mu'mineen Umm Salama said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
56,"""The apparel dearest to Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was the shirt.”",,,56,"Umm Salama said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
57,"""The apparel dearest to Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was the shirt he used to wear.”",,,57,"Umm Salama said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
58,“The sleeve of the shirt of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) extended to the wrist.”,,,58,"Asma bint Yazid said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
59,"“I came to Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) in a group of fewer than ten men from the Muzaina tribe, so that we might pay homage to him, and his shirt was set loose (or: “the button of his shirt was set loose”), so I inserted my hand in the breast of his shirt and I touched the Seal.”",,,59,"Mu'awiya ibn Qurra reported that his father said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
60,"""The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) came out leaning on Usama ibn Zaid, wearing an outer garment of coarse cotton fabric, which he had thrown on loosely, then he led them in the ritual prayer.”",,,60,"Anas ibn Malik said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
61,"""When Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) donned a new garment, he would call it by its name, then he would say: 'O Allah praise be to You, as You have clothed me with it! I beg You for its goodness and the goodness of what it has been made for, and I take refuge with You from its evil and the evil of what it has been made for!’”",,,61,"Abu Sa'id al-Khudri said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
63,“The apparel dearest to Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was the hibara [striped garment of Yemenite fabric] that he used to wear.”,,,63,"Anas ibn Malik said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
64,"“I saw the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) wearing a red garb, as if I were looking at the sheen of his legs.” Sufyan said: “I think it was a hibara [striped garment of Yemenite fabric].”",,,64,"Awn ibn Abi Juhaifa said that his father said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
65,"""I never saw anyone among the people more handsome in a red garb than Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), when the hair of his head was touching close to his shoulders.”",,,65,"Al-Bara’ ibn ‘Azib said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
66,"“I saw the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) wearing two green garments.""",,,66,"Abu Rimtha said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
67,"“I saw the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) wearing the tatters of two sheets which had been dyed with saffron, but had lost their color....” (This tradition is part of a longer story.)",,,67,"Qaila bint Makhrama said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
68,"Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): “You should acquire white clothes, so that your living ones may wear them, and you can shroud your deceased in them, for they are among the best of your clothes.”",,,68,"Ibn 'Abbas said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
69,"“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'Wear white, for it is most pure and pleasant, and you must shroud your deceased therein'.”",,,69,"Samura ibn Jundub said:",رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم كے لباس کا بیان
